2025-07-30 10:56:42.323075 | controller | Also=, or Alias= settings in the [Install] section, and DefaultInstance= for
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323091 | controller | template units). This means they are not meant to be enabled or disabled using systemctl.
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323096 | controller |
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323100 | controller | Possible reasons for having these kinds of units are:
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323104 | controller |  A unit may be statically enabled by being symlinked from another unit's
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323113 | controller |   .wants/, .requires/, or .upholds/ directory.
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323117 | controller |  A unit's purpose may be to act as a helper for some other unit which has
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323120 | controller |   a requirement dependency on it.
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323124 | controller |  A unit may be started when needed via activation (socket, path, timer,
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323127 | controller |   D-Bus, udev, scripted systemctl call, ...).
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323131 | controller |  In case of template units, the unit is meant to be enabled with some
2025-07-30 10:56:42.323134 | controller |   instance name specified.
